# MedicalPower Development Rules

## Documentation Requirements

When making changes that affect architecture, database schema, infrastructure, or introduce new services:

1. Update `docs/CHANGELOG.md` with a dated entry describing the change
2. Update `CLAUDE.md` if conventions or architecture decisions change
3. Add ADR in `docs/adr/NNN-title.md` for technology/architecture decisions
4. Update `docs/PLANNING.md` if scope or roadmap changes

## Code Quality

- All UI strings must use i18n keys from `packages/i18n/locales/`
- Never use `any` type without explicit justification comment
- Every service must have `tests/` directory with unit tests
- Test files: `*.spec.ts` (TypeScript), `test_*.py` (Python)
- Minimum 80% test coverage for business logic
- Use Prisma for database schema and migrations
- Shared types go in `packages/types/`, never duplicate across services

## Naming Conventions

- i18n keys: `namespace.context.element` (e.g., `patient.field.fullName`)
- API routes: `/api/v1/<plural-resource>` (e.g., `/api/v1/patients`)
- DB tables: `snake_case`, plural (e.g., `patients`, `case_study_links`)
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `PatientList.tsx`)
- Services: kebab-case directories (e.g., `patient-service/`)

## Git Commits

Format: `<type>: <description>`
Types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, infra, chore

## Security

- Never commit secrets, passwords, or API keys
- Use `.env.local` for local secrets (gitignored)
- PHI/PII fields must be noted in schema comments
- All API endpoints require authentication unless explicitly public
